(1) South Street, north from, but not including Fletcher Street, as viewed from the 120 Wall Street Building, and showing a general view of the area with the Brooklyn Bridge projecting over the roof tops. Also shown (right), are piers jutting into the East River.

October 3, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing a limited view of the area (from Maiden Lane to Fulton Street only). Also seen are piers 15, 16 and 17 East River. This view is as seen from the 60 Wall Street Tower.

July 28, 1933.
